2. Academic Deficiencies. - A student who obtains one or more of the following
grades in semester final result is considered academically deficient, namely: -

(a) an ‘F / XF’ grade in any course;

(b) Semester GPA less than 2.00;

(c) CGPA less than 2.00; and

(d) ‘I’ (Incomplete) grade in any course;

3. Disposal of Academically Deficient Students

